    "name": "RSS Trends Analyzer",
    "description": "# RSS Trends Analyzer - API Test Suite\n\nThis Postman collection is designed to verify the reliability, performance, and fault tolerance of the **RSS Trends Analyzer** serverless function. The suite ensures the system correctly handles concurrent data ingestion, date-based filtering, and AI-driven semantic grouping.\n\n## Test Objectives\nThe collection validates the following core architectural requirements:\n\n* **Schema and Payload Validation:** Ensures the API correctly enforces input constraints, such as mandatory fields for `rssUrls` and `categories`, and range limits for the `topN` parameter.\n* **Fault Tolerance and Resilience:** Confirms the system remains operational when encountering network latency or invalid RSS sources. It verifies that timeouts (10s) and connection errors (ENOTFOUND) are isolated and reported in the metadata without failing the entire request.\n* **Semantic Grouping Logic:** Validates the ability of the Claude Sonnet model to identify and aggregate similar news stories from different providers into a single trend with a `sourceCount >= 2`.\n* **Dynamic Classification:** Tests the system's \"Zero-Shot\" capabilities by using custom categories to ensure the AI adapts to user-defined classification criteria rather than fixed labels.\n\n## Response Structure Verification\nTests are included to confirm that every successful response adheres to the required JSON format:\n* **Results:** Contains structured trends including `category`, `topic`, `sourceCount`, `sources`, and `headlines`.\n* **Meta:** Provides execution telemetry, including `totalArticlesProcessed`, `totalSourcesQueried`, and a detailed list of `failedSources` for transparency.\n\n## Technical Specifications\n* **Endpoint:** `https://rss-trends-serverless-ds-challenge.vercel.app/api/analyze`\n* **Method:** POST\n* **Runtime:** Node.js 20 on Vercel Functions\n* **LLM Provider:** Anthropic Claude Sonnet API",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "53401328",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/53401328-a1c85b55-1ef9-4e0a-98e6-2f8b835a231f?source=collection_link"
  },
